  <his_func>&lt;p&gt;The secretary assisted the Governor of these settlements. He had the right to correspond directly with the Gentlemen X of the West India Company (WIC). He had to keep a list of notarial deeds and put on notarial instruments.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;From 1772 Demerara had its own secretary. From 1776 there were two of them: one for political affairs and another for judicial and notarial matters.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;#160;&lt;/p&gt;</his_func>
